    <descript>
      <abstract>This polygon layer represents 1990 Census Boundaries of Metro Corridor and station areas.</abstract>
      <purpose>1990 Census boundaries represent a hierarchy of statistical areas used to report and summarize demographic information.  Census blocks are the smallest, most basic unit of the census geography.  Blocks are aggregated into block groups, and those in turn into census tracts.</purpose>
      <supplinf>Additionally, this coverage contains areas the County has identified that define Metro corridors and station areas (a subset of the corridors). Neighborhood Service Areas (NSA) are also identified in this layer. The six (6) themes mentioned above are represented by regions in the census coverage and it is recommended that region outlines are used instead of arcs and polygons, which are included only as the "building blocks" of the coverage.  Attributes facilitate linking the block, block group, tract and NSA regions to external data tables storing demographic data useful for thematic mapping and analysis. Annotation is also available for most of these themes. The coverage NSA contains buffered polygons for plotting the boundaries of the CENSUS coverage NSA regions.</supplinf>
    </descript>
